{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:04:38.719Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining the `/admin/users` Page**\n\nI'm currently focused on defining the scope for the `/admin/users` page. My goal is a frontend-only preview for user and role management. The plan includes a user list, role filters, client association, and a status and permissions summary. I've begun to consider the `client_admin` role.\n\n\n**Clarifying Role Definitions**\n\nI'm now clarifying user role definitions for the `/admin/users` page. The existing `mock-data-model.ts` uses different role names than those specified, so I must ensure consistent naming in the UI and state. I plan to add local-only actions such as invite, role change, deactivation, and reset previews. No real security or backend calls will be implemented; a clear notice will be included. I'll maintain a secure UI feel, and I will run lint and build. I am confirming an existing, extremely basic `/admin/users/page.tsx` exists.\n\n\n**Designing the `/admin/users` Layout**\n\nI'm now diving into a design overhaul of the `/admin/users` page, intending to replace the current basic setup with a premium, custom layout that fully implements UI requirements. I've drafted a short internal design plan. The narrative establishes a secure, enterprise-grade administrative console for user management and RBAC. The visual metaphor will be a secure enclave credential management terminal with a dark, high-contrast aesthetic. I will include KPI panels and a customizable datagrid.\n\n\n**Refining the `/admin/users` Design**\n\nI'm currently refining the layout for the `/admin/users` page, focusing on its structure and interactive elements. I'm prioritizing clean action menus that will either pop open or render in detail panels. I've broken down the page into top, metrics, and main workspace sections. The main workspace will be a bento-grid layout, with an interactive user directory and an access control/audit panel.\n\n\n**Planning Interactive User Actions**\n\nI'm now detailing interactive user actions on the `/admin/users` page. \"Invite New Operator\" will trigger a modal with input fields. Selecting a user in the table dynamically updates a permissions summary and security tokens on the right detail card, with real-time role changes reflecting immediately. Each action button has frontend-only updates, with instant table updates and success messages for a fully interactive experience. I also must ensure mobile responsiveness.\n\n\n**Confirming Mobile Responsiveness**\n\nMobile responsiveness is looking good; the bento-grid layout stacks well on smaller screens. I've confirmed that the table renders cleanly within a horizontally scrollable viewport container, and the detail card moves below the table. The focus now shifts to rebuilding `app/admin/users/page.tsx` entirely, so I can implement the detailed designs. I have checked for existing client data, and found a rich list of `previewClientAccounts` in `lib/mock-data-model.ts`, which I will use to define local user state. I'm now defining user roles.\n\n\n"}}
