o UI elements for a user list. I'm focusing on displaying permissions, roles, statuses, clearance levels, and FIDO2 state. I'm considering visual cues for active, pending, or inactive statuses and FIDO2 registration. I'm also ensuring the layout will allow for easy filtering. I'll need to figure out how to represent user clearance and FIDO2 state in the user card.\n\n\n**Structuring User Console Elements**\n\nI'm now integrating permission details and incorporating dynamic status and FIDO2 state within the user list cards. I'm building out a permissions matrix based on the mock data, including distinct displays for \"gff_admin\", \"client_admin\", and \"client_member\" roles. I'm exploring adapting the table styles and filter structures found on other pages within the admin section, ensuring a cohesive design across the interface.\n\n\n**Constructing KPIs & Filters**\n\nI'm now integrating a critical notice banner about the frontend-only RBAC simulation. Next, I'm defining a KPI overview grid displaying system account counts, including active/total users, admins, client roles, and active FIDO2 sessions. I am then building an interactive filter and action bar that has a search input, role filters, status filters, and an \"Invite System Operator\" button. I am considering the key icon.\n\n\n**Designing User Data Tables**\n\nI'm now focused on constructing the user table with a high-fidelity list of operators, and a dedicated right panel for audit and access control. I'm building out a contextual audit and access control panel, that displays detailed user clearance levels. I'm implementing inline elements, like profile pictures with initials, enterprise tenant links, security role badges, and session state dots. I am also working on adding action icons for quick updates. I am considering toggling activation, and role-change buttons.\n\n\n**Implementing Action Features**\n\nI am now adding action features. I've designed a button to deactivate users, and another to simulate hardware token resets. A premium real-time permissions board is also being worked on, displaying cryptographic scopes with granted and denied indicators. Finally, I will implement a simulated invite modal.\n\n\n\n"}}
