{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:07:42.543Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Assessing Length Discrepancy**\n\nOkay, I'm trying to figure out what's going on with this size limit. The error message is suggesting the input is far larger than it seems, so I took a look at the data. I'm finding that the actual size of the drafted text is significantly less than the error indicated. It seems my working draft is around 25000 characters or less.\n\n\n**Refining Code Conciseness**\n\nI've determined the discrepancy likely stems from formatting or a system miscount. My draft is concise, yet exceeding the limit. I'm now focused on writing a more elegant, compressed `app/admin/users/page.tsx` file to get within the character limit. My goal is a polished version, under 6000 characters, while retaining essential functionalities: user list, role filters, client associations, status indicators, and permissions summary.\n\n\n**Designing Compact Structure**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in designing a compact structure for the `app/admin/users/page.tsx` file, aiming for under 6000 characters. I'm focusing on dynamic updates for user previews, specifically for invites, role changes, deactivations, and access resets, all handled locally. I've cleared the backend/auth phase notice. The goal is a secure, premium, and polished feel. I'm prioritizing minimal JSX clutter, clean state mapping, and modern styling.\n\n\n**Implementing Data Structures**\n\nI'm now implementing the core data structure. I'm focusing on defining the `Operator` interface with fields for `id`, `name`, `email`, `role`, `client`, `status`, and `clearance`. I'm starting the `INITIAL_OPS` data, but have only included the first three operators. I've chosen to use `lucide-react` icons for clear visual representation within the UI.\n\n\n**Defining User Permissions**\n\nNow, I'm defining user permissions and filtering functionality. The `PERMS` object establishes permissions based on roles like `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, and `client_member`. I've added state variables for user management: `ops`, `selectedId`, `search`, `roleFil`, `statusFil`, `toast`, `isModal`, and form fields. My next focus is on implementing the filtering logic and user interaction handlers.\n\n\n**Adding Invite Functionality**\n\nI've just added invite functionality to the code. I'm using state variables for new user details and a form handler to create new operator entries. Invites are handled by generating a unique ID and updating the user list with new data. I'm focusing on clean state updates and clear feedback for the user after a successful invite submission. This now includes input validation and toast notifications for success.\n\n\n**Implementing User Management**\n\nI've just added the remaining user management features. I've implemented handlers for role updates, deactivation, and password resets, including comprehensive state updates and informative toast notifications. The handlers efficiently modify the user list based on the actions taken. I am pleased with the responsiveness of the UI updates.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:07:42.559Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"7jjerp2c","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/admin/users/page.tsx","new_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useState, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport { previewClientAccounts } from \"@/lib/mock-data-model\";\nimport { \n  Search, Plus, User, Shield, Check, X, ShieldAlert, \n  Key, Mail, Fingerprint, Lock, Unlock, UserX, UserCheck, RefreshCw, Info\n} from \"lucide-react\";\n\ninterface Operator {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  email: string;\n  role: \"gff_admin\" | \"client_admin\" | \"client_member\";\n  client: string;\n  status: \"active\" | \"inactive\" | \"pending\";\n  clearance: string;\n}\n\nconst INITIAL_OPS: Operator[] = [\n  { id: \"usr-001\", name: \"Alexander Mercer\", email: \"a.mercer@apex-sovereign.gff.ai\", role: \"client_admin\", client: \"Apex Sovereign Group [Preview Client]\", status: \"active\", clearance: \"LEVEL III (SANDBOX)\" },\n  { id: \"usr-002\", name: \"Dr. Sarah Vance\", email: \"s.vance@governance.gff.ai\", role: \"gff_admin\", client: \"GFF Central Enclave\", status: \"active\", clearance: \"LEVEL V (SUPERUSER)\" },\n  { id: \"usr-003\", name: \"John Miller\", email: \"j.miller@global-retail.gff.ai\", role: \"client_member\", client: \"Global Retail Enclave [Preview Client]\", status: \"active\", clearance: \"LEVEL II (OPERATOR)\" },\n  { id: \"usr-004\", name: \"Marcus Vance\", email: \"m.vance@sovereign-logistics.gff.ai\", role: \"client_admin\", client: \"Sovereign Logistics Unit [Preview Client]\", status: \"pending\", clearance: \"PENDING SYNC\" }\n];\n\nconst SCOPES = [\n  { id: \"global:root\", label: \"Global Enclave Root Access\", roles: [\"gff_admin\"] },\n  { id: \"write:governance\", label: \"Mutate Guardrail Policies\", roles: [\"gff_admin\"] },\n  { id: \"manage:users\", label: \"SSO Directory Management\", roles: [\"gff_admin\", \"client_admin\"] },\n  { id: \"read:telemetry\", label: \"Access Live Workload Telemetry\", roles: [\"gff_admin\", \"client_admin\", \"client_member\"] },\n  { id: \"write:projects\", label: \"Provision Sandbox Enclaves\", roles: [\"gff_admin\", \"client_admin\"] }\n];\n\nexport default function AdminUsersPage() {\n  const [ops, setOps] = useState<Operator[]>(INITIAL_OPS);\n  const [selectedId, setSelectedId] = useState(\"usr-002\");\n  const [search, setSearch] = useState(\"\");\n  const [roleFil, setRoleFil] = useState(\"all\");\n  const [statusFil, setStatusFil] = useState(\"all\");\n  const [toast, setToast] = useState(\"\");\n  const [isModal, setIsModal] = useState(false);\n\n  const [nName, setNName] = useState(\"\");\n  const [nEmail, setNEmail] = useState(\"\");\n  const [nRole, setNRole] = useState<\"gff_admin\" | \"client_admin\" | \"client_member\">(\"client_member\");\n  const [nClient, setNClient] = useState(\"\");\n\n  const selected = ops.find(o => o.id === selectedId) || ops[0];\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (toast) {\n      const t = setTimeout(() => setToast(\"\"), 5000);\n      return () => clearTimeout(t);\n    }\n  }, [toast]);\n\n  const handleInvite = (e: React.FormEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (!nName || !nEmail) return;\n    const newId = `usr-0${ops.length + 1}`;\n    const newOp: Operator = {\n      id: newId,\n      name: nName,\n      email: nEmail,\n      role: nRole,\n      client: nRole === \"gff_admin\" ? \"GFF Central Enclave\" : nClient || \"Apex Sovereign Group [Preview Client]\",\n      status: \"pending\",\n      clearance: nRole === \"gff_admin\" ? \"LEVEL V (SUPERUSER)\" : nRole === \"client_admin\" ? \"LEVEL III (SANDBOX)\" : \"LEVEL II (OPERATOR)\"\n    };\n    setOps([newOp, ...ops]);\n    setSelectedId(newId);\n    setIsModal(false);\n    setNName(\"\");\n    setNEmail(\"\");\n    setToast(`SUCCESS: Registered SSO invite envelope for ${nName} (ID: ${newId}).`);\n  };\n\n  const handleRoleChange = (userId: string, r: \"gff_admin\" | \"client_admin\" | \"client_member\") => {\n    setOps(ops.map(o => o.id === userId ? { ...o, role: r, clearance: r === \"gff_admin\" ? \"LEVEL V (SUPERUSER)\" : r === \"client_admin\" ? \"LEVEL III (SANDBOX)\" : \"LEVEL II (OPERATOR)\" } : o));\n    setToast(`SUCCESS: Directory role for ${ops.find(o => o.id === userId)?.name} elevated to ${r.toUpperCase()}.`);\n  };\n\n  const handleDeactivate = (userId: string) => {\n    setOps(ops.map(o => o.id === userId ? { ...o, status: o.status === \"active\" ? \"inactive\" : \"active\" } : o));\n    const op = ops.find(o => o.id === userId);\n    setToast(`SECURITY EVENT: ${op?.status === \"active\" ? \"Revoked keys for\" : \"Restored access for\"} ${op?.name}.`);\n  };\n\n  const handleReset = (userId: string) => {\n    setToast(`FIDO2 ROLLOVER SUCCESS: Re-keyed physical HSM credentials for ${ops.find(o => o.id === userId)?.name}.`);\n  };\n\n  const filtered = ops.filter(o => {\n    const matchSearch = o.name.toLowerCase().includes(search.toLowerCase()) || o.email.toLowerCase().includes(search.toLowerCase()) || o.client.toLowerCase().includes(search.toLowerCase());\n    const matchRole = roleFil === \"all\" || o.role === roleFil;\n    const matchStatus = statusFil === \"all\" || o.status === statusFil;\n    return matchSearch && matchRole && matchStatus;\n  });\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"space-y-6 text-white pb-12 font-sans\">\n      {/* 1. Database & Auth notice banner */}\n      <div className=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-500/10 via-amber-600/5 to-transparent border border-amber-500/20 rounded-xl p-4 flex gap-3.5 items-start\">\n        <div className=\"p-1.5 bg-amber-500/10 rounded-lg text-amber-400 shrink-0 border border-amber-500/10\">\n          <ShieldAlert className=\"w-4 h-4\" />\n        </div>\n        <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n          <h4 className=\"text-[10px] font-bold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-widest font-mono\">\n            Cryptographic Sandbox Simulation (Phase 4 Oversight)\n          </h4>\n          <p className=\"text-xs text-white/70 leading-relaxed max-w-5xl\">\n            This administration panel demonstrates frontend role management and local-only Role-Based Access Control (RBAC).\n            Database syncing, real OAuth2/SAML SSO integrations, and HSM key distribution are scheduled for the Phase 5 infrastructure deploy.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      {/* 2. Page Header */}\n      <div className=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center justify-between gap-4\">\n        <div>\n          <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n            <span className=\"h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#00FFC2] animate-pulse\" />\n            <span className=\"text-[9px] text-[#00FFC2] font-mono tracking-widest uppercase font-bold\">\n              Secure Oversight Console\n            </span>\n          </div>\n          <h1 className=\"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white font-mono uppercase mt-1\">\n            System Operators & RBAC\n          </h1>\n          <p className=\"text-xs text-white/50 mt-1\">\n            Audit clearance credentials, change user roles, trigger FIDO2 rollover keys, and link sandbox tenants.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n\n        <button\n          onClick={() => setIsModal(true)}\n          className=\"flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-[#00FFC2]/10 hover:bg-[#00FFC2]/20 text-[#00FFC2] border border-[#00FFC2]/30 hover:border-[#00FFC2]/50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-xs font-mono font-bold transition-all hover:shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(0,255,194,0.15)] shrink-0 self-start md:self-auto\"\n        >\n          <Plus className=\"w-4 h-4\" />\n          INVITE OPERATOR\n        </button>\n      </div>\n\n      {/* 3. Toast alerts */}\n      {toast && (\n        <div className=\"bg-emerald-500/10 border border-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-300 rounded-xl p-3 flex items-center justify-between animate-fadeIn text-xs font-mono\">\n          <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n            <Fingerprint className=\"w-4 h-4 text-emerald-400 shrink-0\" />\n            <span>{toast}</span>\n          </div>\n          <button onClick={() => setToast(\"\")} className=\"text-white/40 hover:text-white transition-colors\">\n            <X className=\"w-4 h-4\" />\n          </button>\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      {/* 4. Filter bar */}\n      <div className=\"bg-[#040406]/90 border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-4 flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 justify-between items-stretch md:items-center\">\n        <div className=\"relative flex-1 max-w-sm\">\n          <Search className=\"absolute left-3 top-2.5 h-4 w-4 text-white/30\" />\n          <input\n            type=\"text\"\n            placeholder=\"Search operators, emails, linked clients...\"\n            value={search}\n            onChange={(e) => setSearch(e.target.value)}\n            className=\"w-full bg-[#08080c]/60 border border-white/10 rounded-lg pl-9 pr-4 py-2 text-xs text-white placeholder-white/30 focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#00FFC2] font-mono\"\n          />\n        </div>\n\n        <div className=\"flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-xs font-mono items-center\">\n          <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n            <span className=\"text-white/40 uppercase font-bold text-[9px]\">Role:</span>\n            <div className=\"flex bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-0.5\">\n              {[\"all\", \"gff_admin\", \"client_admin\", \"client_member\"].map((r) => (\n                <button\n                  key={r}\n                  onClick={() => setRoleFil(r)}\n                  className={`px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-[9px] uppercase font-bold transition-all ${\n                    roleFil === r ? \"bg-white/10 text-[#00FFC2]\" : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white\"\n                  }`}\n                >\n                  {r === \"all\" ? \"All\" : r.split(\"_\")[1]}\n                </button>\n              ))}\n            </div>\n          </div>\n\n          <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n            <span className=\"text-white/40 uppercase font-bold text-[9px]\">Status:</span>\n            <div className=\"flex bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-0.5\">\n              {[\"all\", \"active\", \"pending\", \"inactive\"].map((s) => (\n                <button\n                  key={s}\n                  onClick={() => setStatusFil(s)}\n                  className={`px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-[9px] uppercase font-bold transition-all ${\n                    statusFil === s ? \"bg-white/10 text-white\" : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white\"\n                  }`}\n                >\n                  {s}\n                </button>\n              ))}\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      {/* 5. Split Main Workspace */}\n      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-6 items-start\">\n        {/* Left Panel: Table directory */}\n        <div className=\"lg:col-span-8 bg-[#040406]/80 border border-white/5 rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-2xl backdrop-blur-sm\">\n          <div className=\"px-5 py-3 border-b border-white/5 bg-white/[0.01] flex items-center justify-between text-xs font-mono\">\n            <span className=\"font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-white/60\">Operator Directory</span>\n            <span className=\"text-white/30\">Total: {filtered.length} entries</span>\n          </div>\n\n          <div className=\"overflow-x-auto\">\n            <table className=\"w-full text-left border-collapse font-mono text-xs\">\n              <thead>\n                <tr className=\"border-b border-white/5 text-[9.5px] uppercase text-white/40 tracking-wider bg-white/[0.01]\">\n                  <th className=\"py-3 px-4 font-bold\">Identity</th>\n                  <th className=\"py-3 px-4 font-bold\">Tenant Association</th>\n                  <th className=\"py-3 px-4 font-bold\">Role</th>\n                  <th className=\"py-3 px-4 font-bold\">Status</th>\n                  <th className=\"py-3 px-4 font-bold text-right\">Clearance</th>\n                </tr>\n              </thead>\n              <tbody className=\"divide-y divide-white/[0.03]\">\n                {filtered.length === 0 ? (\n                  <tr>\n                    <td colSpan={5} className=\"py-12 text-center text-white/30\">\n                      No aligned operators match active directory filters.\n                    </td>\n                  </tr>\n                ) : (\n                  filtered.map((op) => {\n                    const isSel = op.id === selectedId;\n                    return (\n                      <tr\n                        key={op.id}\n                        onClick={() => setSelectedId(op.id)}\n                        className={`cursor-pointer transition-all border-l-2 ${\n                          isSel ? \"bg-white/[0.03] border-l-[#00FFC2]\" : \"border-l-transparent hover:bg-white/[0.01]\"\n                        }`}\n                      >\n                        <td className=\"py-3 px-4\">\n                          <div className=\"font-bold text-white\">{op.name}</div>\n                          <div className=\"text-[10px] text-white/40\">{op.email}</div>\n                        </td>\n                        <td className=\"py-3 px-4 text-white/60 text-[11px] truncate max-w-[150px]\">\n                          {op.client}\n                        </td>\n                        <td className=\"py-3 px-4\">\n                          <span className={`inline-block px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[9px] rounded font-bold uppercase border ${\n                            op.role === \"gff_admin\"\n                              ? \"bg-rose-500/10 text-rose-400 border-rose-500/20\"\n                              : op.role === \"client_admin\"\n                              ? \"bg-[#009DFF]/10 text-[#009DFF] border-[#009DFF]/20\"\n                              : \"bg-zinc-500/10 text-zinc-400 border-zinc-500/20\"\n                          }`}>\n                            {op.role.split(\"_\")[1]}\n                          </span>\n                        </td>\n                        <td className=\"py-3 px-4\">\n                          <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n                            <span className={`h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full ${\n                              op.status === \"active\" ? \"bg-emerald-400 animate-pulse\" : op.status === \"pending\" ? \"bg-amber-400\" : \"bg-zinc-500\"\n                            }`} />\n                            <span className=\"text-[10px] uppercase font-bold text-white/60\">{op.status}</span>\n                          </div>\n                        </td>\n                        <td className=\"py-3 px-4 text-right text-white/50 text-[10px]\">\n                          {op.id}\n                        </td>\n                      </tr>\n                    );\n                  })\n                )}\n              </tbody>\n            </table>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Right Panel: Detailed permissions & action controls */}\n        <div className=\"lg:col-span-4 space-y-6\">\n          <div className=\"bg-[#040406]/95 border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-5 space-y-4\">\n            <div className=\"border-b border-white/5 pb-3\">\n              <span className=\"text-[9px] text-[#00FFC2] font-mono font-bold uppercase tracking-widest flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n                <Fingerprint className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" /> SECURITY PROFILE AUDIT\n              </span>\n              <h3 className=\"text-sm font-bold text-white mt-1 font-mono uppercase\">{selected.name}</h3>\n              <p className=\"text-[10px] text-white/40 font-mono\">{selected.email}</p>\n            </div>\n\n            <div className=\"space-y-3 font-mono text-[11px]\">\n              <div className=\"flex justify-between border-b border-white/5 pb-2\">\n                <span className=\"text-white/40\">Credential Status:</span>\n                <span className=\"text-amber-400 font-bold\">{selected.clearance}</span>\n              </div>\n              <div className=\"flex justify-between border-b border-white/5 pb-2\">\n                <span className=\"text-white/40\">Tenant Boundaries:</span>\n                <span className=\"text-white font-bold truncate max-w-[150px]\">{selected.client}</span>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n\n            {/* Simulated Live Controls */}\n            <div className=\"space-y-3 pt-2\">\n              <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase font-bold tracking-wider block\">\n                Administrative Directives\n              </span>\n\n              {/* Action 1: Change Role */}\n              <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                <label className=\"text-[9.5px] font-mono text-white/50 block font-bold\">Assigned RBAC Role:</label>\n                <div className=\"grid grid-cols-3 gap-1 bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-0.5\">\n                  {([\"gff_admin\", \"client_admin\", \"client_member\"] as const).map((r) => (\n                    <button\n                      key={r}\n                      onClick={() => handleRoleChange(selected.id, r)}\n                      className={`py-1 rounded text-[9px] uppercase font-mono font-bold transition-all ${\n                        selected.role === r ? \"bg-white/10 text-[#00FFC2]\" : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white\"\n                      }`}\n                    >\n                      {r.split(\"_\")[1]}\n                    </button>\n                  ))}\n                </div>\n              </div>\n\n              {/* Action 2 & 3: Reset / Toggle state */}\n              <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 pt-1 font-mono\">\n                <button\n                  onClick={() => handleDeactivate(selected.id)}\n                  className={`py-2 px-1 border rounded text-[9.5px] font-bold flex items-center justify-center gap-1 transition-all ${\n                    selected.status === \"active\"\n                      ? \"bg-rose-500/10 hover:bg-rose-500/20 text-rose-400 border-rose-500/20\"\n                      : \"bg-emerald-500/10 hover:bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400 border-emerald-500/20\"\n                  }`}\n                >\n                  {selected.status === \"active\" ? (\n                    <>\n                      <UserX className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 shrink-0\" />\n                      DEACTIVATE\n                    </>\n                  ) : (\n                    <>\n                      <UserCheck className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 shrink-0\" />\n                      ACTIVATE\n                    </>\n                  )}\n                </button>\n\n                <button\n                  onClick={() => handleReset(selected.id)}\n                  className=\"py-2 px-1 bg-white/5 hover:bg-white/10 border border-white/10 text-white/80 rounded text-[9.5px] font-bold flex items-center justify-center gap-1 transition-all\"\n                >\n                  <Key className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 text-amber-400 shrink-0\" />\n                  RESET FIDO2\n                </button>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n\n            {/* Live permissions Summary */}\n            <div className=\"border-t border-white/5 pt-4 space-y-2\">\n              <span className=\"text-[9.5px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase font-bold tracking-wider block\">\n                Cryptographic Clearance Scopes\n              </span>\n              <div className=\"space-y-1.5 max-h-[160px] overflow-y-auto pr-1\">\n                {SCOPES.map((scope) => {\n                  const allowed = scope.roles.includes(selected.role);\n                  return (\n                    <div key={scope.id} className=\"flex items-center justify-between p-2 rounded bg-[#020202]/40 border border-white/5 text-[10px] font-mono\">\n                      <span className=\"text-white/70\">{scope.label}</span>\n                      {allowed ? (\n                        <span className=\"text-emerald-400 font-bold bg-emerald-500/10 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-[8px]\">\n                          ALLOW\n                        </span>\n                      ) : (\n                        <span className=\"text-zinc-500 font-bold bg-zinc-500/10 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-[8px]\">\n                          LOCK\n                        </span>\n                      )}\n                    </div>\n                  );\n                })}\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      {/* 6. Invite Operator Modal */}\n      {isModal && (\n        <div className=\"fixed inset-0 bg-black/85 backdrop-blur-md flex items-center justify-center p-4 z-50\">\n          <div className=\"bg-[#0a0a0e] border border-white/10 rounded-2xl w-full max-w-md overflow-hidden shadow-2xl font-mono p-6 space-y-4\">\n            <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between border-b border-white/5 pb-3\">\n              <h3 className=\"text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-white flex items-center gap-2\">\n                <UserCheck className=\"w-4 h-4 text-[#00FFC2]\" /> Invite Operator\n              </h3>\n              <button onClick={() => setIsModal(false)} className=\"text-white/40 hover:text-white\">\n                <X className=\"w-4 h-4\" />\n              </button>\n            </div>\n\n            <form onSubmit={handleInvite} className=\"space-y-4\">\n              <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                <label className=\"text-[9px] text-white/50 block font-bold uppercase\">Name:</label>\n                <input\n                  type=\"text\"\n                  required\n                  placeholder=\"e.g. Jane Doe\"\n                  value={nName}\n                  onChange={(e) => setNName(e.target.value)}\n                  className=\"w-full bg-[#020202]/60 border border-white/10 rounded-lg px-3 py-1.5 text-xs text-white placeholder-white/20 focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#00FFC2]\"\n                />\n              </div>\n\n              <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                <label className=\"text-[9px] text-white/50 block font-bold uppercase\">Secure Email:</label>\n                <input\n                  type=\"email\"\n                  required\n                  placeholder=\"e.g. j.doe@apex-sovereign.gff.ai\"\n                  value={nEmail}\n                  onChange={(e) => setNEmail(e.target.value)}\n                  className=\"w-full bg-[#020202]/60 border border-white/10 rounded-lg px-3 py-1.5 text-xs text-white placeholder-white/20 focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#00FFC2]\"\n                />\n              </div>\n\n              <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                <label className=\"text-[9px] text-white/50 block font-bold uppercase\">Target Role:</label>\n                <div className=\"grid grid-cols-3 gap-1 bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-0.5\">\n                  {([\"gff_admin\", \"client_admin\", \"client_member\"] as const).map((r) => (\n                    <button\n                      key={r}\n                      type=\"button\"\n                      onClick={() => setNRole(r)}\n                      className={`py-1 rounded text-[9px] uppercase font-bold transition-all ${\n                        nRole === r ? \"bg-white/10 text-[#00FFC2]\" : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white\"\n                      }`}\n                    >\n                      {r.split(\"_\")[1]}\n                    </button>\n                  ))}\n                </div>\n              </div>\n\n              {nRole !== \"gff_admin\" && (\n                <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                  <label className=\"text-[9px] text-white/50 block font-bold uppercase\">Client Account:</label>\n                  <select\n                    value={nClient}\n                    onChange={(e) => setNClient(e.target.value)}\n                    className=\"w-full bg-[#020202]/60 border border-white/10 rounded-lg px-2 py-1.5 text-xs text-white focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#00FFC2]\"\n                  >\n                    <option value=\"\">-- Choose Sandbox Tenant --</option>\n                    {previewClientAccounts.map((c) => (\n                      <option key={c.id} value={c.name}>\n                        {c.name}\n                      </option>\n                    ))}\n                  </select>\n                </div>\n              )}\n\n              <div className=\"flex items-center justify-end gap-3 pt-3 border-t border-white/5 text-[10px]\">\n                <button type=\"button\" onClick={() => setIsModal(false)} className=\"text-white/40 hover:text-white\">\n                  CANCEL\n                </button>\n                <button\n                  type=\"submit\"\n                  className=\"bg-[#00FFC2]/10 hover:bg-[#00FFC2]/20 border border-[#00FFC2]/30 text-[#00FFC2] px-4 py-1.5 rounded-lg font-bold\"\n                >\n                  DISPATCH INVITE\n                </button>\n              </div>\n            </form>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n"}}}
